########################################################

DOCUMENT();

loadMacros(
	"PGstandard.pl",	# Standard macros for PG language
	"MathObjects.pl",
	"PGML.pl",
	"parserPopUp.pl",
	"parserMultiAnswer.pl",
	"weightedGrader.pl",
	"source.pl",			# allows code to be displayed on certain sites
	"PGcourse.pl", 	 # Customization file for the course
);

#######################################################
#Setup

TEXT(beginproblem());

$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

Context("Numeric");		# or Complex

#---------------Tolerance------------------#
Context()->flags->set(
tolerance=>.02,
tolType=>'relative');  #relative or absolute

#-------------- Image Scaling---------------#
$imgScale = 0.2;
$width = $imgScale*2000;		#aspect ratio
$height = $imgScale*1000;

#---- Random variables for this problem --------#
$lengthA = random(1.5,2,0.1);
$lengthB = random(3,3.5,0.1);
$mass = random(5,10,1);
$force = random(5,10,0.1);
$freq = random(10,15,1);
$kA = random(25,50,1);
$kB = random(25,50,1);
$time = random(5,20,0.1);

#---- Formulas to compute answers --------------#
$A = $force/($kA*($lengthA/2)**2+$kB*(2*$lengthB/3)**2-$lengthB**2*$mass*$freq**2);

#---- Answers to the problem -----------------------#
$ansA = $A*sin($freq*$time);

########################################################;
#PGML

BEGIN_PGML	

[@ image( "20-R-VIB-DY-32.png", width=>[$width], height=>[$height]) @]*

A L-shaped bar of negligible mass is pinned to the ceiling by the corner at point O. 
Arm A, length [`L_A =`] [`[$lengthA]`] [`m`], has a spring [`k_A =`] [`[$kA]`] [`N/m`] 
attached halfway and a force [`F =`] [`[$force]cos([$freq]t)`] applied at the end of the bar. 
Arm B, length [`L_B =`] [`[$lengthB]`] [`m`], has a spring [`k_B =`] [`[$kB]`] [`N/m`] attached 
2/3rd of the length down the bar and a mass [`m =`] [`[$mass]`] [`kg`] at the end of the bar.
Given that initially the bar is at rest and unstretched, find the angle at [`t =`] [`[$time]`] [`s`].

[`\theta =`] [____]{"$ansA"} [`rad`]

END_PGML

ENDDOCUMENT();
